snippet.textDisplay: Loved this! So awesome!!! I remember my daughter loved Hamilton & Lin Manuel Miranda...when I finally splurged on tickets (never have been able to pay down that credit card balance so probably is costing so much more in interest..ugh...), everything was working out perfectly. Monday-browsing tickets & saw 2 seats for Wednesdays show 7th row middle section in front! Jumped on them along w/parking directly across from the theatre, although we got a bit rerouted due to construction on way there from PA, arrived into theatre w/5 min to spare. Usher said, wow you have great seats..I said I know right! I was so excited to see my daughter's face seeing Lin...only to find out he was not in it!!! I about died! I would have never gone into debt if I had known Lin wasn't in it...however, I must say I still enjoyed it, cried my eyes out! Met the cast afterwards..they were great!!! The best thing was, my friend from college (a costume designer on Broadway who had worked w/Lin in the past) was able to meet us after work & we went out to dinner! Best day ever even though we did not get to see/meet Lin!!!

snippet.textDisplay: Oh my - This was amazing.   We had tix for Hamilton in NYC for my birthday in early March - before the Broadway closed.   Two other shows ( Come from Away and Six, and 3 nights at my favorite hotel.  Two weeks before my husband had a BIG heart attack and we could not go. I had to sell the tickets at a loss and thank God I did....on the date we were to be at Hamilton my husband was back in the hospital.  SO, THANK YOU FOR THIS....I felt it was as much for me as it was for that adorable Aubrey. Thank you to the whole cast, Lin Manuel Miranda, and John Krasinski and Emily for making my day. And making us all smile !!!
